Call for Papers - LDV-Forum, Volume 22, Number 1, 2007

For the spring issue (2007) of the LDV-Forum, the official journal of=20
the Gesellschaft f=FCr Linguistische Datenverarbeitung, e.V. (Society =
for=20
Computational Linguistics and Language Technology), we call for the=20
submission of articles. Contributions may come from all relevant=20
fields in computational linguistics and language technology, as for=20
example:

- basic theoretical or methodical issues in computational linguistics=20
  and language technology
- corpus linguistics and its applications
- text technology and text mining
- linguistic methods in multimedia and multimodal systems
- standards in language and text technology
- syntax-oriented methods (parsing, POS-tagging, morphological=20
  analysis)
- language-processing systems and their applications (e. g. in=20
  eLearning)
- curricula in computational linguistics and language technology=20
  (concepts, study programs)
- presentation of research projects or research groups

Articles should be 10 - 20 pages long (in the LDV-Forum style).=20
Before publication they will be reviewed by at least two members of=20
the editorial board of the LDV-Forum. Style files are available for TeX=20
and MS Word. Articles may be written in English or German. Further=20
information may be found on the website of the GLDV=20
(http://www.gldv.org).

Deadlines for LDV-Forum 22(1) (2007):

      January 31st, 2007: submission of articles
      March 31st, 2007: notification of acceptance
      May 31, 2007: publication of LDV-Forum 22(1) (2007).

Submission should be sent to the editors of the LDV-Forum (see be-
low). Please contact the editors if you have any question regarding=20
article style or content:

